    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Judd</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 61.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Berlin,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 7, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch, No. 68, dated March 14, is
                            received.</p>
                <p>I enclose herewith copies of letters between Mr. Sundell, consul at
                            Stettin, and myself in relation to the blockade of the port of
                            Swinemünde.</p>
                <p>I hope that the advice I gave Mr. Sundell will meet your approval</p>
                <p>Respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>N. B. JUDD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
